\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't know how many rooms were in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh four rooms I suppose, the front room, the kitchen. And the same upstairs. Front and - front and back bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have like a little lean-to or a scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We had a bit of thing me - a thing me father made. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was only two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Bedrooms. Large garden. Which entailed a lot of work and was mostly supporting the large family we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did anybody else live in the house besides your parents and your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, nobody else, there was no room for them. Only room for the cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother have anybody to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Only the daughters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 All done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother or your father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 All. My mother mended everything. My father attended to the - shoes. Soled and heeled everybody}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s shoes - and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about making the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - we used to get a woman in. For anything special. Ordinary stuff was done at home. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Suits you mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh buy the suit, but - as regards - our men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s clothes, used to have}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431  dressmaker in. A Miss Griffith}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
. I don't know if you remember her or not. From - I don't if it from Water Street or not, down that part. And - she had - you know, she was doing the rounds. Most people had her seven days a week could make an appoi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 ntment with her. Miss Griffith}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431  is coming next week - next Tuesday, so - look out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But your mother would do the mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd have new clothes for you, you wouldn't have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Never had second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 hand clothes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you used to hand ones down in the family though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, that's the - that's the beauty of large family you see. Specially with boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We had new shoes but we had to take great care of them and me father to - repair every shoe in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would your mother go to buy you clothes and shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh she had a - a fancy place but I can't remember who. Whether Gra
nts came in it or not. Oh John Phillips, John Phillips. John Phillips was a - was a great caller in our house. Remember him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he used to come around the door with his goods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. In fact - he - had Grants actually in the beginning. Latterly any way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they come round the doors with the clothes or come every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Used to come round the door - occasionally and - if you fancied anything they'd bring a - article and you could see it and judge it for the quality of the cloth and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And your father did all the shoe repairs at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he do any cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No cleaning, but - I mean - no - I mean no - help with the - what do you mean, spring cleaning or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or ordinary jobs like making the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh fire, yes, he was adept - adept at the fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He wouldn't help with the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. I never remember him-doing. I do more than what me father did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, very useful. Anything special he'd get a man in. And there was nothing very special in Cotton Row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So your father would do it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he do repairs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Anything done - he'd do it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You said he built the lean-to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I never - I - no, he didn't build - I don't think he built anything. But as regards repairs he might - have a go at anythin
g. He used to keep all our shoes repaired. Cobbler and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he ever dress you or undress you as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. I think he did. Yes. He was most useful man at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember in which way he helped your mother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well he'd help mother most ways - it was possible for a man to help. He was a most what's the word - useful man. Nothing too much trouble. And it don't matter how tired he was, he'd worked a double shift, he'd come home tired out, if there was anything w
anted doing it'd be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He helped to bath us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, he was great on reading. Yes. Yes, newspapers or anything - very particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he tell you any stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, oh he used 
to have - stories by the ream. Yes. Of his boyhood days more especially, down in - the country and that kind of thing. Most interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he tell you stories before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes, before we went to bed. Or a wet night we couldn't go out and - it'd be stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he take you out on your own without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, often times. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not - not long walks, we - well, when we went out - we went out as a family to the beach or something of that. Taibach beach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But he would take you out sometimes without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he look after you if she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any jobs you had to do yourself to help your mother and father in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well us might get coal up and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have a particular job, did you all have separate jobs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What - we had - in Cotton Row we'd a long garden and we all mucked in there - giving my father a hand. It w
as a lot of work I mean it helped - it helped the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Keep you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. We'd never have done without it. Wages and pay in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any jobs to do in the house yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not particularly, only used to muck in like the rest of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the older children help the younger ones with dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the younger help the older in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well they - they tried to. You know sometimes they were more hindrance than worth it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes, rigid. Rigid times. No playing about, it - something had to be very special - before we'd be allowed to stay up. We had homework or something like that yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother put you to bed or anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well she must have in the beginning you see, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember your father putting you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember when you put yourself to bed, how old you'd be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, brother - our brother maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember now how the bedrooms were shared out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, no. No I don't remember. Yes, small in any case, there wasn't many rooms there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not all the children were born there were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well you see some of the - it all depends on the ages. They went out to service some of them you see. That's as it was in those days. And they - their room was kept - taken up by us then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You four boys probably all shared a room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And the youngest, the baby with the mother and father was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, that's it, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Be none of you downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. We had to - make the best we could of the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember who was sharing the bedroom with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Llewellyn. And Sid I expect. All the boys. Yes, four boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have a room to bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not in Cotton Row we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would you bath then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 After everybody went to bed we'd bath in the kitchen. In front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Every week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 There was bath night was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Saturday night mostly. It all depends on the - queue. Who - who was going to go Friday nig
ht and who was Saturday night. When you've got a crowd there it's a job to manage it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What used to happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - a zinc bath you know in front of the fire. And - everybody go to bed except the one that's bathing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You went off in turns then did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have clean clothes to put on after the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. We had - all ready on a - on a - a stool by the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the kitchen. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The same room, the one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, and - and it'd be full with the crowd - the crowd that we were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever eat in any other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 On very special occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When a relative called perhaps. And that not often. Very rarely we ate - we ate anywhere but in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would it be a range or a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, a little - coal oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 A fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 With an oven alongside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And - and right from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She didn't have a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How many would be there at breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well all depends on the times. I mean some of my sisters were out in service you see. Well we h
ad their room then, I mean there'd be more room for the boys to play about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh, just before we went to school. We were called to go to school and if we didn't get up in time we'd be - late getting the breakfas
t. Or perhaps we wouldn't have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would that be about eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, round about. If not before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were near the school weren't you in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would all the children be together having breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 As many as
 we could - put by the table. And - or very often we couldn't get 'em all - get 'em all there. 'Cos me father - me father wouldn't be there because he'd be at work. Me mother would be - looking after us, there'd be one - there's two places more for us. So
 the boys would - be children then would have benefit. At the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you all come in and have it together or would the first down eat it and then go and then the others come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I - I think that - first come first served kind of business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your father would have his earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well he'd be at work do you see, he'd get up early. We wouldn't see him until night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you usually have to eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - well, plain - plain enough food. We'd have toas
t. We'd have bacon. I don't say you'd have bacon and eggs, you might have had it - had it sometimes when - not often. Bacon or a bit of ham a special. Plain enough food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about Sunday, would you have different food for breakfast on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, we'd have a good dinner on Sunday, have a - we'd have a joint and so on. Make it a - something special on a Sunday. And \{
ILLEGIBLE\} and - or cakes at the weekend - would be made galore. Specially made for weekend and - overlap during the week. With a big family of course you can't bake everyday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you have to drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about your midday meal, did you all come home midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes. There was nowhere else to go then, no school - meals in schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you have for dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh we'd have a dinner. Most - most day - days of the week we'd have a - what we'd all a dinner, potatoes and - veg and so on. Meat of some sort. 'Course the Sunday meat would last us - a day or two af
ter Sunday. And a bit of new stuff added to that helped things along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you reckon you'd have meat every day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I don't say we'd have it every - we might have a bit of fish - in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have liver or faggots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, no. We maybe have a change - no, no, I don't remember much about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you ever have rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, we'd have a occasional rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't get it from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, we'd have it from a fellow in the same street very often. He might be poaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't know how he got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, we wouldn't care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have to pay him for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. And sometimes we paid more than it was worth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd have your breakfast and your main meal midday, what would you have after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - go to school in the afternoon, come home all - all hours \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 come home they'd all - all the grown ups had had their food. It was a - free for all afterwards, get what you could.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Just take what you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have a sitting down meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Oh I'd sit down, yes. Very strict on us coming to meals - even if there wasn't a - a big fat table there. But everybody had to be in his place for a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You had to sit down to have a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You had a meal in the evening then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, a snack. Call it a snack. 'Cos they - they were afraid you'd dream to much if you had a big meal you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. For years she did. Until she failed, then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But she would be baking her own bread in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The oven in the kitchen, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I don't remember her making jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Latterly - in - latter years, but not when we were kiddies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Pickles - with any stuff in the garden, onions and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would she make wines?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Any beer brewed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. They were dead nuts against beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You said you had a garden so you grew your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And a good garden it was and - and we all mucked in, we all helped our father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there any fruit in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Currants and gooseberries. Yes, blackcurrants and redcurrants and gooseberries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother and father buy any fruit as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh that was a rare treat then in those days, because we used
 to have plenty of fruit in the garden, there's gooseberries, blackcurrants as I said. Strawberries sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That was a help wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you don't remember having tinned vegetables, and tinned fruit only rarely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. tinned vegetables - ever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you keep any livestock like hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We kept pigs. In Cotton Row, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, we all helped - me father was the boss. \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 often helped to clean - clean the sties out. Get fresh bedding - straw and all the rest of it. And helped with the food.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You killed them for food did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Always nice to have a pig hanging up in the passage when we went - that's the pig, or in - or - or a pig carved up - ham.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That's where you used to hang it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who killed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Dan Jeremy was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your father would kill it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You see, yes, Dan Jeremy didn't come - no. He w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 as a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 pt at that job. Killed no - no end of pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And then you'd hang it up to cool it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. It'd be hanging up to - they used to say that the best picture in the house - was half a side of bacon hanging up. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't have chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, we never had them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you had quite a lot of meat then, you probably had meat nearly everyday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Nearly every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember your mother ever having less food than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Many times. Never nothing said about it. But we took it all in, we knew - we knew what was happening. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You noticed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your father have more food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 My father was very abstemious. He - he worked hard in this time but \{ILLEGIBLE\} took advantage of that in - regards fee
ding. No, he took his share, I mean, like we all did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you were conscious of your mother having less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh very often. Very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you allowed to talk during the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - not a lot. If we did start to chatter - we were soon pulled up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Practically - eat what was put before you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did your parents say if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Wel
l they wasn't very pleased about it. It all depends on the condition at the time. Whether - if we were - a bit off the mark well you'd he excused, but if you were all right - there'd be something to be said - why didn't you clear your plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If there was something on the table that you wanted like the salt could you ask somebody to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or would you have to wait until they offered it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, ask somebody to pass it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Provided it were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would it be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
On occasions no. With a big family it isn't - it was asked out in the beginning. To see how far it goes, sometimes there's very little left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And sit in a certain way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Sat in the same place. At the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You all had your places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You kept to the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes - as - when - when there was - humanly possible anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you bring a book or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. You could but it would be - frowned on. No. Off the table with your things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not before everything was - so. You don't - wouldn't have to ask permission
. Perhaps you get a bit unruly by waiting and they say, now - if you - if you've had enough you'd better clear off. That kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And you all sat at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How was the meal served, did your mother serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. No she did, she did all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And your sisters or just your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Me sisters weren't always at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So your mother really served the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, she was the chief. And if there were any sisters of course they'd always give her a hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What order would she serve in, would she serve it from the pot or would she have it all out on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh all - all ready on the plates. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd serve it and she'd put it all out before she called you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. That's it. That's it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She wouldn't serve your father first, and then Llewallyn and then you and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd put it all out and you'd come and get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the younger brothers and sisters, where would they sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not far from mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Or the older girls you see. When they were home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they used to be by you at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes - if there was room. Because there were so many and a small kitchen. Sometimes had to have a relay. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who would go in first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Father and mother. Would push us, they - follow in afterwards. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The children would be served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Then the father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 With the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you ever all get together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
With a - with a squeeze but a small table put against the old kitchen table. Yes. Bit of a squeeze sometimes. But - often times my mother would prefer
 - being on her own feet and looking after the family and have a snack of her own afterwards. Yes. Have a bit of peace and quietness as she said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember that happening often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She preferred that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd serve you all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Look after herself afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Splendid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If you had any worries you could go to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. Very - lovely type. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Always. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, he was good too. And - at night time - specially wintertime we'd - he'd go through his boyhood days, stories galore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You said you could say anything to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If you had any worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes. Oh he was splendid type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did they expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well, I don't know how they expected but - we behaved - not that I - I say it but we behaved as a child should - should - to their parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Respectfully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Always harmony at home. Of course there are - there are differences in certain families but - nothing worth speaking of, only the ordinary friction you get. Which is only - only nature isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they say you could hit back or not if somebody else hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well they used to tell us to look after ourselves. Don't come here with your tales, you're big enough now to look after y
ourself, kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They were hoping for the best I'm sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they stress character or jobs, or what do you think they really wanted you all to become?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well I don't know they stressed anything in particular, but they - they - the behaviour was a great thing with 'em. How we behaved. And - great thing was about attending a place of worship. Me father was a - oh he was - fanatic in that respect. And we all
 followed him, I don't say we were fanatics. You can't call him - a man a fanatic if he follows him as he should. But they were keen - at the time we - started to go to church, not supposed to miss a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh well they frowned on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We'd - we might start but - we were soon cut down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't allowed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well we would be told off, we might get a - a smack too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well my mother you know might give us a bit, but I don't - I don't think my father ever - I don't know, he might have - give us a smack with a stick on the behind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember any occasion?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. Nothing starting like that, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't ever remember being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, the only punishment that - that we dreaded was put to bed early. That was worse then anything, that's worse than the stick.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember being put to bed early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, several times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 For what sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh perhaps telling a fib. Being caught out. Caught out telling fibs and that you know, what you do when you're young, you say anything and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember how you felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Felt round about that size. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you say you received the ideas on how to behave from both your parents or from your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - no, both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't think one of them played a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, I think they were both of - of a kind. Yes. Very good, both of them, that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would your birthday be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. Big fuss. But wouldn't have very expensive stuff there. I think
 the food would be about the same as usual except - you may have couple of extra - types of cake or something of that kind. And a jelly or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But they always used to make a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, 
of a kind. Not very expensive. Oh perhaps something to wear. I was going to say a pair of garters but I'd better not say that. Anything that - anything that was useful. You have a new suit, no, no, not a new suit but perhaps new trousers, new pair of shoe
s, a new cap, or a new collar or tie.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have anybody to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Very often we used to. Although we didn't have much room with our own family but we used to squeeze a couple of guests in. When we were kids. Yes. Well we used to like tha
t, we used to be very - we were very fond of kiddies coming to the house. As long as they behaved themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 On your birthday you could take somebody home to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember doing anything specially on Christmas Day with your father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not any specially - but Christmas Day - with us was a big day for - church services you see. In those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Can you remember Christmas Day in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I used to go - I'll tell you why, I used to always go an
d knock up my aunties and uncles living close by to see any Christmas boxes about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have different food on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, we'd have the Christmas fare, as far as we could go. Yes, Christmas pudding and - so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you do anything with your mother and father particularly on Christmas Day, you'd go to church wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, we would pull the place about when we get home afterwards. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would your father and mother join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, as far as they could. They - nobody didn't mind as long as we - we - enjoyed ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not in the early days. Llewellyn had a - an accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 n. Yes. And he fancied his chance as a player. And he used to play very often much to \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well 'cos we said - we said he couldn't play it properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was that the only instrument in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I think it was. We never - we didn't have a piano in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well we were all members of the choir, church choir, in our turn. 'Course when we were very young of course we didn't think of a choir. But as we grew up each one in turn joined the choir - in church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever sing at home, make music together in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, oh yes. Sing - sing-songs sometimes. All types of songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you sing together on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, and Saturday night perhaps. Yes. Have a sing-song. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would your parents play games with you sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - within reason you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember anything particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, nothing like fussy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Plenty of books. Plenty of books. 
Always - well we've - we've got them here now - lot of them. And you used to have books as prizes in those days you see. The school and Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 For good attendance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And behaviour. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You got a lot of books that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Newspapers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He used to get the - one newspaper a day I think. I'm not sure what - what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it the Mail?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well I don't know about the Western Mail, occasionally read the Post or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not very particular I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No church paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The only church paper we used to have was the Parish Magazine. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you ever remember your mother or your father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Me father used to
 read to my mother. Very often. But we'd go in there on the quiet, you know, quiet evening. And he would be - be sitting you know beside the table and the old chap'd be reading to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would he be reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh Bible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could she read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She couldn't read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes, sometimes, well - it all depends what he was reading. Sometimes he wanted - to emphasise something he had - he had in his hand at the time he would - some story of so
me kind, but never - newspaper never. He objected to us reading a newspaper in a way, there was so much - stuff in the - in the newspaper he'd object to the child reading that very often. So we didn't have much chance with newspapers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But he used to have a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes, not - not like we do today, have two or three knocking about. He did have a - newspaper occasionally. The old - the old Echo or the old Post or whatever it was in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, we had - two I think. I don't remember much about them, I was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You can't recall anything about it, what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They were the two little brothers were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember a funeral from Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 From West End?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relatives, you had relatives in Cotton Row did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. No, I don't think we were ever taken out to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You used to go in and out the houses did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh yes, we went - we had - relatives at Cotton Row, when we lived in Cotton Row. Lived in the end house - the nearest the old mill you know. Oh we always - were mucking - mucking in and out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were never taken anywhere with your mother and father to visit people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sometimes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who would take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Be very small then, always with mother to see relatives you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In Port Talbot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, when mother used to go. Station Road. The - weekly shopping place you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Very often, not often, not every time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes, on occasions. Well the great thing in those days was - picnics in - on the beach. Families. And that was an annual event. Not an annual, be two or three during the season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would your mother and father go with you or just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh they were both - for these picnics. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the summer holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, it would be a family affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd all go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. All that - all that was available you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Which beach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Taibach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not Port Talbot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, no. Taibach. And - we wondered about the weather weeks beforehand. Whatever the weather was in the morning we used to start off, down we'd go. Even if the rain poured and sent us home, but we'd get down there. We were satisfied then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you take and food and everything with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Often take our food back and - got into it at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd walk down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. To Taibach beach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It wasn't so far?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you go in the water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Play on the beach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well a good day of it. Provided the weather was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would that be on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mostly Bank Holiday. That was an annual event. Bank Holiday - you were expected to go to the beach at Bank Holida
y, doesn't matter what the weather was. And many times you went down at the Bank Holiday it wasn't fit to leave the house, but - we did it. Because we used to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever go on any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We used to have a choir outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You had Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sunday school outings were the chief event of the year. As regards as - as far as I'm concerned. 'Cos - I had the arranging of them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about when you were a little boy in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember going on an outing there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We used to go to Margen then. But I - I - I got further than Marg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 n since I used to arrange it myself. 'Cos in the old days - when we went to Market we went by lorries. All the farmers used to l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 o
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 an
 their lorries, they'd rig them out. Put a - you know, all seats on them. Rough seats so the children could sit down. Just for the day. But that - that passed. The old wagons were - there were a few accidents with the old wagons, the - seats collapsed, ve
ry often sometimes the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
s legs were - well not fractured but badly cut, and they did away with the wagons. Then they went to buses. And - in fact we had - on one outi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 ng - by Richards, the furniture}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431  removal - removal van. An packed the kiddies in like sardines in it. But then we got the - wagon again and we had buses.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But before the war you would go in farmers lorries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Used - used to rig up temporary seats on the - on the wagons. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And you'd you'd go to Margen Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, go to Margen and to Vickers Park. But - you thinking of it now as a very unsafe thing to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not when I was young, not when we was young, no. No, I can remember our first holiday. I suppose our neighbours to
gether - the year before that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When would you first holiday be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - I think I was married I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The early days? Well - it all depends on the season. If it was a fine season - we'd spend half our time in the - in the water, bathing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't far from Taibach beach were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. And not only the beach, the - the old float. Used to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 and ba}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ther there at Sutton Park there, it was all right for bathing. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about Saturdays in the winter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Wel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 l in the winter then - well - di}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 d the best you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sunday, oh well we had to behave ourselves on Sunday, had to do - had to do as we're told. Well we used to do as we were told every day 
- but more so on Sunday. It was already planned. Sunday morning church. Sunday afternoon Sunday school. Sunday evening - church again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. We had our best clothes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well - they never worried - they were never very strict about that kind of thing, playing - well we never had any obvious games on Sunday any case, play about the h
ouse, make ourselves a nuisance. But work - well there again it was awkward if you - if you were on a certain job in the works. Only you were a certain man, a - mechanic or whatever, were expected to work on a Sunday. Otherwise -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your father have to work on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Most - most Sundays. I don't remember him ever being off on a Sunday. I've seen him - working all day Sunday, coming home at six Sunday evening - unable to go to church. Go to bed for two hours. Back in work at ten o'clock at Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What was he doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I don't know what his job over - over - I can't remember his job in - in - in the old - the oil fuel works. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But your mother would take you to church would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. My mother - and father - left t
he house on Sundays - together. They'd walk - when we was in Cotton Row - in - West End, they'd walk up as far as Griffith's bridge then they'd part. My father would turn le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 t to go to church. Me mother would turn right to go to Every Sunday night. Parting of the ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She was Independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And he was Church in Wales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How often would they go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well whenever possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - my mother went c
hapel every Sunday night. Whether me father - whether my - father was able to go or not? If she was well enough she'd be there, she'd never miss a chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you children went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 To church, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 None of you went with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No. We might have gone when we were very tiny. I think I do - I do remember something about that, going to chapel there when I was very small. Don't remember much about it though. I remember the - comfortable seats there, the pews. We - we used to pla
y with the doors. It was so comfy there. That's all I remember about that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And then you went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. The whole family went to church except me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She still kept going to the Welsh Independent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How often did you go to a place of worship, would there be week night services as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Always, me father wasn't working - he always attended - went to Evensong. And I as a member of the choir I'd always be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd go 
to a - I think it'd be Monday night - the meetings of the Gibeon. She'd go, she'd attend, yes, most week - most services - most weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And I was Secretary of the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - for many many years. I - I - well I'd better not start that, I'd fill a book on all I was going to say about myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you going to Sunday school when you were in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes. Yes. I've got a book in my pocket now - a prize 
I was given in Holy Cross Sunday School. That's the only Sunday school in the parish at that time church Sunday school, I got it in my pocket, you can have a look at it if you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it Welsh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, it's English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there Sunday school outings then from Holy Cross?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Our outing was mostly the Whitsun outing. To Glamorgan. That - that was - were sufficient for the year. It's only recently they have extra outings, I mean Porthcawl or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you didn't have them when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was only the Whitsun tea at Margam Castle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Whitsun tea - was the chief thing. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You used to go there every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any other social activities organised by the church that you took part in when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not when I was little but - I mean, since I - yes. But no - only - no, nothing much for children bar the Whitsun time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 There was nothing in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. They - they used to have - penny readings as they called them in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Little - impromptu - speeches and - and - recitations and - you know, getting - come and see them together. And - who'll sing for me now and so - kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 An impromptu concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How often would they be held?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Practically every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Very regular. And kind of - it was attached to the Band of Hope more than anything else you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You had Band of Hope in church did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would that be once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not very regular. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You belonged to the choir when you were quite a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have to go for practice for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The choir. In the old days you'd have to - be a probationer. Sit in the fr
ont seat in the church on the Sunday - to know all that's going on, to get used to the service or to seen what was said and all the rest of it. After a certain time - if there was a vacancy in the choir they'd ask you and - first of all you had your voice
 
tested - to see if you was fit to - join the choir. Well then, if your voice was all right you'd be asked to join the - the - they - there was - they had - they had two. There was a - there was a special service in those days when boys joined the choir. A
n
d the - after the service you'd be a - become a member of the choir. And - you were expected them to attend all the choir practices. All the service, whether they were weeknight - or - if - if you got to be in a - say the Harvest on the Thursday morning i
f we were able to get away from school with a note to the master you'd do that as well. We used to look forward to that. Yes, well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd have one night choir practice would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 One night. I can't remember what night, I believe it was a Monday 
night we used to have choir practice with Mr Seaton. In the old mission room. And - wonderful man Mr Seaton was. Wonderful man. He'd very bad chest. And we boys knew it. And we played on that. And very often - before he'd arrive in the - schoolroom where 
t
he practice would be held we'd stoke up the fire, put fresh coal on and if the wind was blowing back the place would be full of smoke. And many a time he'd come in, phew, what is this smoke here? You can't expect to have a practice in this room. Go home a
ll the blessed lot of you. And so we all did. Send us all home. And you couldn't do that too often. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the church run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Used to have temperance society here, It was very strong at one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you a member of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes, and I - I - I'd better not tell the story. One fellow who I was very intimate with, he joined. He joined once he joined a dozen times. That's true. I can't think of his name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He couldn't keep it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. He couldn't keep it up that nigh
t. No, impossible. And he was a - a wonderful fellow. Long headed you know, he - he'd talk on any subject. But - his weakness - was his pot. Couldn't help it. He'd go - he'd go every time. And if he get worked up, warmed up, he'd repeat the hymns - half a
n hour late coming out. This fellow, the same fellow. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And then he'd be having a drink after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Have a couple. Used to lodge in - West End. And - and a - a wonderful in his way, he'd talk on any subject. He'd talk on temperance - better than any temperance man you ever heard. Yes he couldn't keep away from the - liquor. Couldn't help it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there much activity in the temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, were very active in those days. Not only temperance but Band of Hope and all that kind of thing. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you do, would it be one night a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh Monday night as a rule. And - we used to go there and everybody would give testimony - like this fellow who - who'd - who would - where you'd been all weekend. Well he'd be 
in church on a Sunday, and he'd be singing like a - like a thrush or that. But - after he come out he was a different chap. Queer isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you belong to any other club organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, they didn't have any other clubs I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, not regularly you see. With a crowd like that - not always sitting down together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 By whom would it be said if you said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Me father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It wouldn't be said regularly like on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. When the occasion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 arose and it was - there was - plenty - plenty of time to think about it. All hustle - hustle and bustle with a crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I don't know 
about taught, we did have - did - always - well, we must have been taught otherwise we wouldn't do it, yes, I'll say yes to that, because we all said our prayers. Religiously before we went to bed. Yes. Otherwise, I mean, the night wouldn't be complete - 
the day wouldn't be complete.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Used to all - yes, we did for some time. I don't - I can't say how long, I can remember my father - didn't matter how - tired he'd be, perhaps working in the - late shift or Sunday, 
he'd get the Bible out the last thing at night and read a fair portion. A prayer and go to bed. But you - you can't always - can't always keep it up you see, with - the way you live. Too tired to go and - speak sometimes. I know he was a terror. How he li
ved so long I don't know. Struggle. Yes, struggle it was, a struggle to live, struggle with the family, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. When you asked him - who did you vote for today? The right man. That's all the reply you'd have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you've no idea what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. I had an idea but - he never told us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't think he was Labour or Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Definitely not. No. By his action and his - his - what he says. No, he was an old timer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But when you were young you've no idea who he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No talk about it in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. She thought - she'd always think we were too young - young to know anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember them voting in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't know what party they voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their jobs, or their houses if they voted differently from their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes. That's why they were so secretive. And there are very few men who tell their children who they voted for. Because the children couldn't keep a secret. It's all very well for a man to say - tell - his mate - tha
t he voted Labour, he didn't vote for Labour. But he wouldn't tell his child that see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You think the men did feel pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. No doubt, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you think your father felt himself under that sort of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, I don't think. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your father or mother were never members of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And they never worked for a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They took no active part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What were their other interests, when they were not working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well - there wasn't much time for my father to spend. He was always doing something. With a large family - a lot to be done. Never used to send a boot to the cobblers. Did all the repair work himself. You see, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 With all of you and the garden and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And the garden, oh - it would be a large - a big garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And he was working long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. No time for anything else then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, I don't think so. No. She never took any interest in politics or any of that kind of thing. No. She'd go to chapel on Monday nights you know to what they call the - this Monday night meeting. Yes, go there pretty often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No women's institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, no Women's Institute in those days I don't think, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. They'd never time. With a large family you haven't got the time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What time would your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well when he was working ordinary shift it'd be six o'clock, six to half past. Well by the time - he get his food, and clean up - it was almost time for bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
He'd go to church regular on a Wednesday night. Wednesday night Evensong you know. However tired he was. But the rest of nights he - the rest of the week he'd be in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he attend any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He - he had a club but - he never - I don't - I don't remember him attended \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 used to - somebody used to take his contribution for him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember him ever going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I don't remember - oh yes, I do remember him going but - oh, it was in the distant past when I was a kiddie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it like a Liberal club or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431  Odd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
fellows or - one of those - what do you call then - friendly societies, yes. No, he wasn't - any political club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Nor a social club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother ever go with him to the Odd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 fellows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or any club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The only time they went together to town was - oh - two - Llewellyn the grocer in Station Road to pay the bill. On a Saturday night, tha
t was the usual run. Out on Saturday nights both of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They wouldn't go to a pub or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Never. Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they call anywhere on the way home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It all depends if they meet somebody - intimate. You'd call 'em
 in for half an hour and - have a chat. But they mostly come - in fact they were - they were so late on Saturday night we used to get too tired to talk when they come home. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. None at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he attend the races?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Not to my knowledge. I don't think so, I mean, not by his attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, a boot club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, only - only thing they belonged to was the church - penny bank. We had penny bank and clothing club running in St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
s for many years. You'd - on a - I don't know if it was a Monday, it doesn't matter about the day, you would have a card at the beginning of the year and you'd go there and y
ou'd pay your shilling, two shillings or half a crown, whatever you want to put on a certain day - you put it on, your card was marked and - that was yours. Well that'd be on for a twelve month. At the end of a year - you look - no money handed out, you'd
 
go to nominate - a tradesman who you were going to buy your stuff from, you see. Assuming you had - two pounds ten in your club. Now you're not going to have two pounds ten from the Treasurer. You can have that two pounds ten in value. You nominated a - a
 grocer or - or outfitter in Station Road at Port Talbot and you get - and you get your stuff from there, and it's paid from the funds. Good isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So this was good for trade, it would encourage the shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes. You went - it we
nt on for years. I don't know why it finish - finished. And then the penny bank again. You get - yes, you get an interest on that. Because it was a Post Office thing. But you were paying that out - at the end of the year. But the - the clothing club - was
 never paid out. Only through the - business people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about a sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, never had a sick club. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, we never had one of those. No. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
All right. We were very happy family. We only - we used to get a - a - a squabble now and again which is only natural, but never anything serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, well it's very difficult to say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Llewellyn was next to you wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, he was my - he was my elder brother of course. I had to keep well in with him 'cos he protect me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about Sid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sid was a good boy. Yes, he was a good boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you particularly close to them or one of the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well we were very close, the whole lot of us. I tell you, we were a lovely family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 As a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well with mates in - Cotton Row and West End.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I suppose every house had children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, in those days, yes. Yes, all types we played with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you play with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, we all - we all joined in in a gang.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not in the yard or garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, mostly in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go in anybody else's home to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
We used to go - go in but - it wasn't - well they didn't like it very much at home. For you to be in the houses. We didn't like a lot of children coming to our house
. Not that we didn't care for children. But you know what I mean - you never know what children - what children carry away - as regards - conversation and that kind of thing. No, we - kept very much to ourselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And your mother didn't like you to go into other peoples houses to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Unless we were very intimate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why do you think that was, did she actually discourage you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - no, she - no. Because I mean we - we considered that ourselves like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your mother and father didn't mind who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, they didn't mind, no, no. But we - we dealt with that ourselves. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you would never go into some peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Oh no. No, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, what we say - wasn't our type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, yes, because nobody could stop us once we had - once we had the oil. But we'd have a good scrubbing get - when we got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - when - as kids? Oh - 
all kinds of games, cat and dog was a very favourite game that time. And puss-puss. Oh - blind man's buff. Well the ordinary games in the street, marbles and that kind of thing and - tops and - whip top and so on. And cat and dog. Cat and dog was a great 
favourite. You don't see it today. They're not clever enough to play that today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well, it is - is a - is - you get a bit of wood that length, point on each end. In the ring. And numbers in the ring. You - you - space your distan
ce out on the ring throw the cat and wherever it lands, whether it's in one, two, three, four, you have five - paces to start with, you run - to hit this - hit the cat. The cat was - a - a piece of wood with pointed sides. And with a - a half a hand broom
 
you tap one end. See 'cos it'd bounce up and hit it. And then you - the distance from the ring was taken by - each chap coming out. See, there was twenty counts on the ring, well it'd be twenty score for you. I tell you it was technical. Oh that was - tha
t was a game those days, don't see it today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you play football or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. In a way. But not so much as today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have a football ball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. We'd have to make a ball. Get a bundle of rags and tie it up tight, and then 
if it was wet - it was a job to carry it it was so heavy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Never used to be any in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - used to spend - when I was a - a kiddie then living in Cotton Row - summertime spend most of the time in the water, float.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We had rabbits some - for a while. But - you wasn't keen on that kind of thing 'cos once they died - a different complexion on the whol
e business. Yes. Weren't too keen after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you collect anything? Like stamps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well I - I do now. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you start as a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, in a small way, but - I've got a wonderful collection now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember it in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. Didn't have any then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You did gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you do all sorts of things in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Very fond of gardening. And it was there on Saturday - Friday and Saturday in our younger days, I used to go
 up to Rivers garden, old Mr Pugnell was the - no, before his time, Mr Morris. Morris the gard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
ner was in charge up there. The master came to me one day in school and he said - Mr Morris wants a boy for the gardens. What do you want to do, I said. Well you
 go up and see him? So I went up to see Mr Morris. And all he wanted was - to take a basket of stuff - to the crachach - Major - Major Grey - and that takes - after school hours, go up there, through the field opposite Eastern School up to Rivers garden, 
a
nd the basket would be ready. You take this - and there was a short cut to Major Grey's house from the gardens, wouldn't have to go down the main road then and up again. Short cut across the hill. Take the basket of stuff there. Couple of coppers for it. 
Then the same thing on Saturday. And perhaps there'd be another customer by the end of the week. Then perhaps he'd have two or three by the following week. So all - extra money you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He didn't pay you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You'd have a tip from the person you took it to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you do that for quite a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And - in those days they used to - they used to grow - grow grapes. Black grapes. And the real crachach were having them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would he sell them to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you do with the money you had then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh save - save up or give it to mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - yes, we did a bit - but - not much of a fisherman I'm afraid. Caught more cold than fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, we used to go for a ramp. To be on the beach was the chief thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were fair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 y near weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes. Yes, yes. The great - the great - the popular thing in those days was the - rather good - for bathing. The end - where the
 river - where the river entered the float. The rail - railway crosses it, the old P.T.R. railway used to cross it. And it was very deep there. That's where - that's where they used to drown all the cats and dogs. It was nothing for boy to go there - and 
dive in, and when he come up, there's a cat or a dog facing him on the top of the water. Been released from the bottom.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Is that where you used to bathe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not a bit. In the float usually though. There was a place there - in the float, you could go
 a long way before you get out of your depth. And it was so - convenient for a boy that are frightened of depth - that they christened it the babies pool. I don't know if it's in existence now or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I always thought it was dangerous down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Certain parts, yes. Well this part, it was a - a - a sandy soil, and you - you - gradually go in and you know exactly what depth you get up to. But other parts -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they let you go down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 We used to do that on our own. Never told them everything. No. We were very careful you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who would go with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh the - the gang from - West End, boys of my own age. Or Cotton Row, wherever we lived at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about bicycling, would you have had a bike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not in those days. But I had a bike since, I did a lot of cycling. I did go cycling - when I was courting, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That was during the war was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes. And to go to Porthcawl on a bike in those days was a wonderful feat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, the only thing football. Mustn't forget to tell you that we took a - a - took a church team to France.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That was later though wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. 1910.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't in school then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Is there enough paper there for that, I could - I could fill a book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember taking part in any sports in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The ordinary sports they'd have, they didn't have much, there weren't much - question of sport in school. He'd - buy a ball - foo
tball - and - ball would last as long as it could. He'd kick it to pieces. Then we wouldn't have another one for two years. And we'd play - in the playground you see. And - the ground was rough, we had any ball that we - if you're playing on a field it's 
quite different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So it wouldn't last long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go to any theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Might go to an odd concert. Nothing - nothing very startling. And then of course we used to have concerts in school. They
 were great events. Each one had his part. Each one trying to out do the other. Oh they were great fun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the - in the Central Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 For St David's Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well ordinary - it was an annual. An annual concert in those
 days. Yes, Syn. Davis was a great man in that respect. Wonderful master. Good sportsman. And a very good sportsman you've got a good fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about music hall, did you ever go to a music hall when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Very rarely. Very rarely. No, I don't think I went - I ever went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, if you can call it pocket money. They couldn't afford much, but whatever we had we were satisfied. Couple of coppers. Because
 we had whatever - whatever we wanted we had at home. And - an extra packet of sweets was - was all right, nice and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have anything regularly, like a penny or ha'penny a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. But - it was in a way regular enough. We could look for
ward to a couple of coppers every week. Yes, but - we couldn't insist on it see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh sweets. And half those would come home and - offer 'em around - they was generally offered round the family, nothing left for you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. We - we were blessed with a couple of good sisters there. And - they did - fiar share to help me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No relations, friends or neighbours would come in to help her would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They would if they were allowed to, they were - we always had good neighbours, but we didn't require them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What if your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well the sisters - my sisters would look after her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. We had relatives in the same street. My father's bro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 
ther was living in the - furthe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 st end of the street. Will George, same as me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you see them often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, every day practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh they used to come to our house or we used to go to their house. Yes, oh - you know, as it particularly in the same street and - sometimes it was all - seeing too much of one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents have any friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Plent
y. All types. Some they liked and - and others - and some they didn't care much about. But you got to take it - the rough with the smooth haven't you. Yes, they were - they had plenty of friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would they see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh they visit us. Yes.
 And we kids - when you got home sometimes be a houseful of what we call strangers. We didn't like it, and only - I mean - relatives of my - mother or my father they were. We kids, we didn't want that. Yes, yes, yes. We'd rather be on our own. Bring our o
wn friends in, our own - our own age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother and father share the same friends, did they tend to be relatives more than outside the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, more - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they have any friends other than relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not a - no, not many. They may have a few but - relatives mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember your mother having any different friends from your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She'd not any of her own friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, no. No. No, a member of a big family then you wouldn't want many friends. I mean, apart from them. Yes, her sisters and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would your father have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. Very reserved type father was. Very reserved. He had no relatives much - here much. His uncle - and my Aunt Julia lived in 
- in - Cotton Row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 This was relatives mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If people came to the house would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, if - if - it all depends on circumstances. At the time. 'Cos we're a large family, and - the nice
ties wasn't always about, and you couldn't offer - well at least my mother wouldn't offer anybody a meal unless the - she thought it was - nice for them. That's the trouble then. Wages were small in those days. The old m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ll Taibach was working, and - if you were getting a guinea a week you had a lot of money. And a big family, see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you remember people coming in and having food with you on any particular days or occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No, no. Anybody that came on a - you know, a spasm, they wer
e always welcome, a cup of tea and whatever - whatever was passing at the time but no special fuss. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Just a cup of tea and a piece of cake or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And we blessed them. Oh we were all right, we didn't mind - who came in as long they were good company, that's the point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But it was quite open house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, always - always open house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents go out like that to other peoples homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No. No. My father never went out except he - to work or to church. Was never see in the town. He may go on a Saturday night with me mother - when she
's going to pay the shop. He'd go then and perhaps he'd - he'd - with a basket of stuff to come home he'd give her a hand then. And perhaps they'd come home with a brake. If the parcel was-too heavy. But not often they came on the brake, it was too expens
ive. You know, a couple of trips in the brake was - if you got a bit of money in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That's why he went up to the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They wouldn't deliver in those days would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. They would on certain days. Then if you f
orget anything afterwards you'd have to go and - fetch it yourself. Do you remember the brakes? Horsebrakes in town. Oh start - start from Port Talbot, then to - right through where we lived and back. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 People often say that in those days you had to make your own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What do you think your parents did, they didn't get together with friends or neighbour did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No, our age - you take - we - were in the church. We'd have something in the m
ission hall. Practically every night in the week. Whether you're interested or not is up to you. Perhaps Monday night would be temperance meeting. Well - everybody isn't going to be a temperance person, but you go there, always have a chat and maybe a lit
t
le entertainment. Then another night be Band of Hope. Another night be debating class. And that kind of thing. Be always something passing. And the girls were looked after. Girls Friendly Society. A very strong in those days. We had house - on the bridge.
 
You know the Taibach Bridge. Well the end house was a - a G.F.S. house. Girls Friendly Society house. It's - it was for - the purpose of looking after girls who came to the town - friendless. And it did a lot of good work in those days but - it passed on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your sisters go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And my wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They used to go there to help the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes, and - there was a - there were a big following. And a person by name of Miss Brooke in charge of them at the time. Wonderful person she wa
s. And that was the - like a meeting house for the young - ladies. And that's where I used to - wait for my - on - on the bridge, that was my a
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If people came to visit your parents would it be just to chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They wouldn't have musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, no, never, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time ; before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - well maybe, I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you think there were different groups of people in Taibach then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Different types? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Like middle class or working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, there were. There were certain groups. But not very - outstanding though I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you feel that people belonged to different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In a way - in a way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You couldn't remember what you thought then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, well - they're a cut above you kind of thing. And really acting that way some of them. They looked down their noses at you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you think they thought of themselves, they'd think of themselves as not working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, they'd think they were a cut above the ordinary you see. And - knowing the history of some of them they wasn't quite as good as 
we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you think you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Ordinary working class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What sort of people belonged to the same group as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, I don't know. All the people I come in contact with are - are in that class I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you ever told to touch your cap to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. In school - the school they saw that - taught that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 To whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well it w
as difficult to say. We couldn't understand it, of course we - we did understand in a way - are we allowed to mention names? Is - the thing is - it all depends you - how you - were towards a certain person, if you were - friendly with 'em you take - remem
ber Major Gray? Well - yes, well now, he was a - real - autocrat. Well now people didn't have much use for him. Now - take another man actually in the same - status -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Major Gray was manager of the works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes. Yes. We'll take Mr Bray th
en. Now - totally different to Major Gray. A real sport he was. Real sport. Talk to any old tramp or anything on the road. But the other, oh no, he'd cut him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In school you were told to touch your cap to certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Major Gray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, but we often didn't see him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you show respect to anybody else like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Clergy - ministers. Yes. Doctors. Doctor Davis. Yes. Always to Doctor Davis. Funny isn't it? Well I'd do the same thing with Doctor Phillips now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anyone you called sir or master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
I - I've got a weakness there. I do call most people sir - if - they're in a certain position. I can't help it now even. I - I - in the office - specially if - if - you shout from the other room, Mr George. Yes sir? Always came natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were brought up in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 To whom would you say sir when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - very likely - well the schoolmaster to start with, Gwyn Davis. Never forget him, and - and the ministers 
or the clergy. Always yes sir, the Vicar. Yes sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. But I can't remember who, I've see it done many times. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't take your cap off to women passing or anything like that would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was only to those certain people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you remember showing respect to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 By either - saluting or - taking their cap off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't remember now who would do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, somebody very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anyone you used to call madam in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Mrs Davis, yes ma'am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When you went with the greengrocery or the produce from the garden you'd deliver it to the kitchen would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the district of Taibach who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Taibach? Well - Major Gray was a big shot. Was a big shot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who else do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Have we counted Major David? Major David.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He was the owner of the tinplate works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, his father before him - was the owner you see, old D.R., we got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2293807\charrsid14304431 
- have we got anything about Dr. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 David? Well you can't put him now because he had died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He'd died by the time you were in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Oh no, no indeed. He - he - he was alive when I was in the - in office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So it was Major Gray, the two Major David's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well it was Colonel - Colonel D.R. David. Major David.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And Mr Gray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Manager of the - the mill at Taibach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The tinplate mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, the tin mill. Copper mill - copper works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who else would you consider important, the most important in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh Doctor Davis, yes, he was - he was - on his own wasn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who else would you think would be important there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well there's nobody in the street, that was the only - that's a popular area for those people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But in those days when you were living in Cotton Row who would you think were the big shots in Taibach? The Vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - yes, it'd be Vicar Jones then I suppose wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you come into contact with Major Gray and Mr Bray and D.R. David?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I wouldn't come in contact with Major Gray. Major Gray - he was a pig of a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't have any contact with him at all really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Only the doctor you'd come into contact with would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Only professionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, and - I used to take vegetables out of the vicar's garden and always a basketful for - for Doctor Davis. I 
never saw Doctor Davis, only saw the maid. Yes. Doctor Davis was a real toff. Nothing - no - nothing very upstart about him, he was a real toff. Not like some of the others, stuck up fellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who would you say they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Major Gray for one. Nobody liked him, I don't know why. He was a mystery man more or less, I don't know - I - I can't fathom it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well in industry. Major Gray was attached to the Williamsons - where there was colliery I don't know, y
es, the colliery I think. Whether that's where his importance came in. Well who were the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mr Bray.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mr Bray, the copper - owner of the copper works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Doctor Davis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Doctor Davis because he was a physician. And he worked for yea
rs for nothing - amongst the poor - he did. He's not like the present day - you call 'em in, bill tomorrow. Wonderful man - good hearted you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They were the important people of Taibach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 There was nobody you thought of as really important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Up to 1918, up to when you were in school, Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any shopkeepers in Taibach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, no - only a very few. And I can't remember who they were, we had a - I know a tailor and a - and a grocer and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they mix with people in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. They were - more or less strangers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would the clergymen mix in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The clergymen were all right, and the ministers. They were part of the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Teachers the same.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was Gwyn Davis living in Taibach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, he lived in Pombril. But he came to us as a sport, and we liked him, all - he was a - a strict - headmaster but he was a good sport.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who did the teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - I don't know. Ex-County school scholars and that kind of - girls and boy that are just leaving school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were they friendly with the people in Taibach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or were they just friendly with the clergymen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh no, I don't - wouldn't be very friendly with the - the ordinary public I don't think. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would the clergyman be friendly with the public?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, he would because - and the ministers, because - they used to do their daily rounds or weekly rounds whatever they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any farmers in the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they mix with the ordinary working classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No farmers were - on their own more or less. They had no time for anything, only farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And then the employers, they were Major Gray - he wouldn't mix with the ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. Excepting Asa Bray. He was a - totally different than Major Gray, Major Gray was a real -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about Mr Bray?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well he was in his - big Wesleyan, very interested in the Wesleyan movement. And - through that, people rallied round him, see. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Major Gray didn't belong to a church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He was - yes, he was a - a - in St Peters, but - very stand-offish. Very stand-offish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So though Mr Bray was a manager he mixed with the people of Taibach really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Bray. Yes, yes. Yes, a good fellow - and his family. I know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - very similar, there were a few crachach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who would you call the crachach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes, yes. Well they were a big noise, Thomas Jenkins himself was a church warden himself at one time at St Peters you see. And that's the type of people that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Shopkeepers on the whole went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes. I'm trying to think who else -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Well, the old - old - old D.R. was a warden for several years. And Mrs David was a big supporter of St David}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s. And so was Miss Annie. They were big church people, big supporters and - and they had gifts and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the people who went to chapel, what sort of people would you say went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - I don't know what styles they were in that time, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where would you say the ordinary people of Taibach went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I - I think the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Chapel rather than church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You wouldn't have many working class in St Peters would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. But - we'd have a lot of the others \{ILLEGIBLE\} there too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 More crachach in church rather than chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes. I don't know whether they cl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431  together or not, must be something in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where you lived in Cotton Row and that area did a
ll the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well it all depend on their standard of living, whether they - some could save from a shilling a week. Other's couldn't save from a
 pound a week. That's the trouble, is the - individual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh there was different groups, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Can you remember a family in the different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Opposites.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were any people thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I can't think - pin point anybody now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were all much of a muchness there were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You said that some would be more saving than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you think some felt superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. I did you know. As they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who do you think would be the superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Anybody who paid a shilling in the work - say anybody in the works more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was definitely between craftsmen was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And - and officials you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And the labourers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It went with the father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You felt that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Oh yes. If you were a boss - you were somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about in the working men, there were people who were skilled and some were unskilled?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well - taking them through and through they were much of a muchness. You'd mix well. It's only the boss - would be the outstanding fellow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you feel there was a distinction between the craftsmen and the labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No, I don't think so. No, there was a good feeling - with most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They both went to different places of worship. Father went to church and mother went to Gib}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
on. And - you couldn't talk about anybody in the house - as regards running anybody down. No. Hold your tongue. Got no right to - pass a remark over anybody. Father the same. And we haven't have we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You mixed all together then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes. Yes. And they used to leave the house on a Sunday night, father and mother. Quarter to six. Go up as far as the bridge and part. One Taibach and the other to church. Funny isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your mother think of herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Just working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Ordinary - type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it possible then to sort of go from working class to middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well there were - there are ways and means.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you remember anybody doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well - they - they'd get it by odd means. If there were any new project in the town and a new committee being picked, this - this - fellow that was out for a - promotion as it were, if he could get on that that'd be the starting point for him. Yes.
 He'd climb from there then. Once - once they had their - their foot on the step - nothing - nothing could stop 'em after. Certain - certain - types of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Could you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Doctor Phillips Owen. He's - he's the only one - or Doctor Davis. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why do you think they were called that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mr Bray. W.A. - W.OA.A.J Bray, he was a toff with his ways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Why do you think they were called real gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well their attitude toward their fellow men. I believe that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anyone described as a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well Mrs David was a real lady but too much of a lady. She only - I mustn't speak disrespect of her - of her 'cos she was very kind to me but taking her generally she was a bit of a - not a snob, but - a cut above others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 She didn't mix easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, although - she was in all the sewing parties and all that in church see. We had Mother's Union and she always attended. She'd bed amongst them like the rest of them. So you can't count her out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived when you were a child? Was there one around cotton Row, West End?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, not - yes, I suppose it was part of his beat but he never lived - lived near us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you would see him around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Because - in Cotton Row, everybody cultivated their own vegetables. We'd good gardens there, and - good prowlers about there too. And be very careful as to - what was missing - missing in the night. And we'd very often have
 a policeman parading, just patrolling. He wouldn't make a fuss, but he'd be there - he'd come around - once or twice a week. Specially if he'd been given a hit that - was - certain things were happening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you think of the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Good. Never looked upon him as a policeman as a - as a pal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your mother would never threaten you by saying, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, because I knew - I knew the policemen, they - they'd spoil me if they arrested me I'm sure. That's the 
attitude I had with them you see. Because - I think it's a mistake to tell a child, look out, there's a policeman coming. They can be great pals to children, and they are too, a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were you brought up to look on a policeman as a friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Because in Taibach you'd know him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes. And old Price - you know Sergeant Price? Oh - used to him right on every committee we had, save us from paying a gateman. Well naturally we put poor old Price by the gate, used to have any nonsense. But he had a way about him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How do you think the policemen in Taibach then treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well all right, except - come a rough - maybe a Saturday night the tough - tough cases on a Saturday night. There - there were figh
ts and that kind of thing but - nothing to bother about. The police had the thing well in hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Cotton Row, well we - Father worked in the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you never saw the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It went with the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 There was no landlord as such, it was a company house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Company, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Always felt it. Always. It's an awful - awful feeling that though isn't it. I
 mean everybody don't get it, but - we - whether we were - ultra-sensitive or not don't know. But we often felt it, that they were having a struggle. They used have a struggle too, there's no question about it. Wages those days under a pound week - someti
m
es. Go up to the mill for our father's wages on a Friday night. Well the girls - take a job in service. My eldest sister - sister, she was up in Pentilar for years. With Frank Smith the architect. Home from home. That's he they treated the maids in those 
days. Like a daughter. There was no regrets the when they - when they go to - earn their living. The great thing of a mother's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Good homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you think about it, that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well we
 felt for it. And I think we tried to help as much as we could. Yes, we did. We had a good garden in Cotton Row. Everybody mucked in. And grew as much stuff as possible to save buying. And it is a save too when you grow your own vegetables and there's a d
ifferent flavour on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Very little. Very little, I don't remember him being out of work. And I don't remember him - los
ing time through illness, he must have sometime, it's impossible to run - all your life without - no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any periods when you felt they were having more of a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well it was all a struggle. Yes. Yes. Is - is a natural thing I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No. Never. Too proud see. This often it - and we're paying towards it, everybody pays towards that in their rates. But them days we - be that think amongst us. And it's all wrong. Yes. Yes. Oh it's thrown at 'em today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But your mother and father would never have help from anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. They'd nobody to help them, I mean, they - they - their relations were poorer than they were. I wouldn't call them poo
r you know but - yes, yes. yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't remember or them ever having any help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The - the - the way be kept the family going was - do his own foot - boot repairs and all like that, all that he could you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anyone in the distri
ct whom people disapproved of very strongly, anybody in Taibach, was there any special way in which they showed it? The people didn't like Major Gray you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there any way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well they cut him. Wherever h
e was, didn't make anything of him. Neither would he make anything of anybody else ever. It would cut both ways you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You used to hear about people being made to leave the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 With their attitude to the public. No, I don't think of anyb
ody, I can't think of anybody. Well Taibach has been a friendly part really. Everybody knows what everybody's doing there, more or less. Know everybody's business. And I think it's a good thing in a way. And I think I know too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You went to school, you were never given lessons by your parents were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No. No. In fact they couldn't give them. My mother was no scholar. My father was pretty good, but - he'd not the time. If he - if he had - if he did a job for money he'd have done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh I don't know, when I went first must have been about five. In the infants school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When you first started what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Half past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When did you go back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Dinner hour, yes, and back by two. And then to half past four I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You went all day as soon as you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Some children went very early at three year old didn't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I never went that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So when you started you went all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was it mixed or boys only?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Mixed in the infants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. And mixed later on too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were near there weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But at West end was a distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But at Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How long did it take you to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh at Eastern, oh - five minutes. Unless you play about the road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, with mates. Either they called on us or we called for somebody else, always go in a gangs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 From Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, I didn't dislike it. Happiest time of my life I think - in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
I did. Yes. And I think it's the happiest time we ever had. Well the - I mean - you - everything was for nothing, and you'd have good company there. And - you know what's going on in school, you go to that and you 
get a good teacher. I mean a good sporting teacher and you're - you're at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you feel about the teachers, how did you feel about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well I had great respect for the teachers. One teacher in particular, Mr Floyd. Remember him? He w
as a - Wesleyan. And - rather a sanctimonious type of fellow. The scripture lesson in the morning was - was a great interlude, was worthwhile. He'd enlarge on what he had read, and it was very interesting. But, I - I'll - you a little story about a - on a
 
Sunday night. You know, we had nicknames for most people. And on - this Floyd, we called him Teddy. What for I don't know. And - we were coming out of - we came out of church on a Sunday night, three or four of us, and these boys were in my class in Easte
r
n, and - Floyd passed. Good night sir. Good night. Oh, that's - yes, go to church, and he's lodging in that cut, and he was coming out of the house as we were passing. And one of the boys saw him, and - come on boys, this fellow said, to the rest of us, c
o
me on, there's Toddy. Toddy, Toddy. We nicknamed him Toddy. And he shouted back at - who called him Toddy? Well nothing in it, but it was no - it was only respectful - we shout at the teacher. And - that was that. Go to school next day. And playtime. I'd 
l
ike to have a word with you just one minute, Toddy says to me you know. Right sir. Well I though, he said, when I met this boys on the Row on Sunday in their best suits, that they'd be all respectable boys. Respectably dressed and I thought their conduct 
w
ould be the same. Why sir? Well - your manner last night - when you passed me wasn't very good for a - boys coming out of church. What did I do sir? I knew what they'd done. They - used a funny expression. They called me a funny name, he said. Nothing in 
i
t, he said, but I expected a bit more respect than that from scholars I'm teaching. That's all, he said. I don't know why he asked me. And I didn't shout. But it went home, I told this boy afterwards, I said, you're nothing to talk about Toddy, I said, or
 - make fun of Toddy on the road. He's the best teacher in school. He was. Floyd was a great teacher. So that was that, I - I got me point over, there was no nonsense after that - not in class even.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important, the manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Tidiness was a great thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, punctuality, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, they'd pull you up. If you were - I mean, there was - sometimes you were apt to speak disrespectful t
o anybody - in a hurry. Not long before they put you up - and tell you how to speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Oh yes. And I think it was good to - learn - lot of 'em want it today - The behaviour of some children are beyond words. It doesn't matter where there and the same attitude they take to anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The teachers were keen on manners then were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, they were. It was like talking to a - a brick wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen, did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 All depend on the teacher. If - if Mr Floyd used the cane he'd use it well. He'd a terror with the cane, but very rarely he used it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did you have to do before he'd give you the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, disobedient - any disobedience in cla
ss or - doing something they ought not to do in the class he'd say get books or get - get ready for something and you go and talk to the fellow behind you, and - he - not heed what he says. That'd be against you, he'd get around with a cane right across y
our back. No words mentioned. That was the answer to it. As good as to say, now listen to me the next time. Words spoken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was he the only one who used the cane in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. A few there. There was one fellow - would rather use the knuckle on your - on yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 ur muscle here. He was Griffith, Owen Griffith}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
, that was his name. He had an awful punch. He come around and he give you one on the arm here, oh you'd feel it. And a bruise there too. No word spoken.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What would you have to do for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh gossip or something you know. Or try and - copy off somebody else's book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they punish the girls the same?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Girls were like mice there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No naughty girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I don't remember any naughty girls in my class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You never remember a girl being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. I can remember the girls in one - in my class very well. Ethel Davis was one. And the Samuel twins. They were in my class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Oh always. Ye
s. And if there was any homework - you - that'd be done before sit down for you - you had your tea. Make sure it's done because after that you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they ask you what you were doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not particularly, they - they used to ask, and we more or less tell them exactly what had gone on. Without asking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
I remember father coming once. I was rather taken a back. Whenever a visitor came to a class, we were told - everybody stand when a visitor arrives.
 So one afternoon master goes to the door, open the door, and a little man comes behind him-and everybody stood up, it was my father. I felt about that size. I never thought he'd do that - it'd apply to him. I told him, well you made us stand up this afte
rnoon will you. Well I tell you what you do - only for me you stood up? No, we stand up for everybody that comes in. Well I shouldn't - why should I be different to - why should I be different to anybody else then? And you know, it took me back a bit.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What did he come to school for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 About - I think my brother leaving - about leaving school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That's the only time he'd visit the school is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you remember your mother visiting the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 They knew all - they used to - they were - acquainted with them, but they never - mixed as it were. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Most of them, yes. Yes. Most of them. Most o
f the kiddies there, their fathers working with my father. That kind of thing. The old mill at Taibach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sometimes. Sometimes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What sort of children, have you any idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Well - it all - it all depend on the mood of the teacher at the time you see. 'Cos they used to - you know, teachers get their spasms sometimes. You can't rely on them from one hour to another. You were a nice little child one minute and 
then you'd be knocked on the head the next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You shouldn't think they'd single out certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, I don't think - they were very fair - on the whole, they were very fair with children. No pets as it were. That's the trouble in school isn't
 it. But I don't see any - I didn't see any pets with us. But if a boy did excellently well or a girl, they'd have praise and that was it. But they wasn't made a - that would finish then with that lesson. They wouldn't keep on that stuff all the week, you
 see, would make you tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. There were gangs. He used to have a lot of boys from the Constant. And they, when they got together it was look out. They were toughs. But they was as good as gold in 
- you know - they wouldn't do anything - dirty then. They were rough and tough, if you were - if you done anything - wrong, and offended them in a way you would expect a punch. Yes. Yes. But nothing else. And - if you were in trouble, the best boys out to
 see - to see you through. If you had a mob after you on - after school on the road, and you get these boys - handy, hey, they'd clear the place. You could settle - to all walk home with us. Yes. Constant boys they were. They were tough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have a gang in Cotton Row?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, we weren't enough for a gang. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How many in the constant gang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh about a dozen. A lot of boys up there then see in those days. Their parents - their father's was all colliers - more or less. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there any children who were left out to things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, I think they all - mucked in as it were. More or less. You get some kiddies and nothing would satisfy them. Some would sit down all day and cry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Were there some like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 One or two. And - yes, but - you didn't notice them. They weren't - up to it, leave them alone. You get tired of all tears.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You went to the Eastern school, that was all the one school wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't go to another school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The County wasn't open was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, it was open. I had - I tried to get there, I tried the entry exam but I flopped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh I don't know, what time - what - what age was it then in those days? Fourteen was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Some sat an exam and left at twelve didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh the labour exam, yes. Yes. No, I don't think I left at - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you don't remember really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, I must have gone the whole hog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I think so - bec
ause - in the meantime, I used to do little jobs on Saturday for the gardener. As I told you, Mr Morris. Go round the cachach with the basket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have stayed on longer if you'd had the chance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. I didn't see any point, I mean if I'
d been at County - or - or higher - higher grade school perhaps I might have, but - I - I didn't see where I had the benefit much by staying there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Yes, I went to - certain classes. Mr Hilbe
rt ran it - do you remember Mr Hilbert? He ran the fishing in the mill Taibach. Very clever man. I went there and had a - I - taught a bit of book keeping with him, a bit of shorthand, and arithmetic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was that immediately you left school or much later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh much later. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 After you left the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Do you now have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 None at all. Apart - well I shouldn't say none at all, I wish I'd had - the higher education. But then - I don't kn
ow whether I'd have been - it would have put me any different to what I am today, you never know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 Do you think that you benefi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ted from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes, definitely. You'd be in a sorry mess if you didn't go to school wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 While you were at school you did have a part time job, it was only that one little jobs was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You - you mean the garden now. How did I get it? Oh I think the - he - Mr Morris Mr Morris come down to the school and 
asked the master did he know of any boy. Used to do it after school hours. I used to go up the - used to go to deliver after school, and many times in the week he wouldn't have anybody, but Saturday - was a regular day. Saturday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He came down to the school and asked Mr Davis?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And Mr Davis recommended you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Very likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 gardenery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 . Go up to the gardens - the - what you call the - the potting shed, and see Mr Morris and ask him what jobs he had. Well he'd have all the stuff ready in baskets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 With him. Oh only an hour or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have to go on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Only Saturday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Not during the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't actually paid at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I had - Morris used to pay me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Half a crown I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you had tips as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Never tipped, they wasn't available anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No tips from the people you delivered it to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Give it all. I knew it'd come back fourfold in one way or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You don't know what it was spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No. If I wanted anything particular I'd tell her. Then she'd get it for me. But if I didn't want anything - well she'd do what she liked with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't working with other people really were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You got on all right with Mr Morris?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You liked him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 He treated you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. He'd be a - a just type of man see. Big Wesleyan. Yes. A big pillar in the Wesley at Taibach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And you liked the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes I did, I got - I'd - I'd liked to have stayed there. Yes, and go right through the whole business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't have a chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, I knew - I'd have to finish in school sometime or other so whenever it came - well, quicker the better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't have another part time job before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Your first full time job was in the mill was it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh in the mill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Is that where you went when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. John Phillips. Remember John Phillips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were a carder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. John Phillips and Grant owned that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - like they did in - most those days. They had their customers, John Phillips had me mother as a customer. We 
were a big family, always something wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was a flannel factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Came to my mother, anything wanted? Have you an order to give me? Could pay when you liked kind of thing spe. Well my mother used to give him an order, whatever
 she wanted, and - paid him in his own way. And then - when I - going to come into now - what was the question you asked me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh well I just - yes, and he'd say something. Your young boy looking for a job? Yes. Well - a j
ob with me if he'd like to come up there. That's how - so that's how it started. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Take out the orders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the mill, in the flannel factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh in the mill? Oh well my first jobs was - a carder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Now - when the wool arrives in the mill - in the old mill, it lies - lies in pieces about that small, all sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 s of pieces, about half a sheep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431  back. It's all cleaned and you know - and - it's got to be put through c
ertain machines, which breaks it all up. The - it goes - kind of a roller running - the opposite direction with - teeth on it, and you put this wood thorough and it - the action of the roller is like fluff coming out the other side. Come out of the roller
 
the other side and it blows it out. Well then - it's taken from there to another department. And this wool - wool now is quite soft like snow you put through rollers and it comes out from this roller - this machine, in threads. And the threads are immedia
t
ely - wound on bobbins like a roller. Well they in turn then - are taken upstairs to the spinners, put on a spinning mule, it's called a mule, in a row. All the threads are - they're - the - they're all that way now at the end of the room, the thread is t
a
ken from here right across the room to a - a bobbin, which goes - quick you know, fastened on that. And after all the threads are fastened up, then the machine is set in motion. And the action of the machine is that these turn fast this side, and the whol
e
 row on the far end moves slowly, to give a chance to the thread to reach the bobbin. And it's twisted and twisted, and the very soft thread to a - well - like a piece of - cotton then. Tough. And when it's on this big roll you can - it was easy to break 
i
t. But it's once it's - spun - it's - you know, it's turned in - and - and would on this bobbin and it's like a piece of cord. And that's the stuff - which go - go to make flannel. You see? After - my process of taking up the - upstairs to be - to be - wo
u
ld or - it goes to weavers. Some hand looms and some machine looms. Well hand looms are laborious things, they're tiresome things, but they did wonderful work on them. But to go upstairs to the loom - to the machine looms, these rollers are put - these bo
b
bins now about that length are put - stuck in and - on - this contraption altogether. Anyway, they ended up - at the - the cloth - the flannel pieces spun, it's - it's made one piece with all these threads. Some crosswise. The others - you know, that way.
 It's a wonderful experience to see it done.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What hours did you work when you first started as a carder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - half past seven to half past five I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would it be everyday and a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, worked 'til one o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't work Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Didn't have pay much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were saying about the day you had off for the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I - I only - I only went to the wedding but - cost me a - cost a morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 That was the boss's wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
And all the girls - see there were about thirteen or fourteen girls there. I was only boy there. Now these girls in those days a girl likes to see a wedding. They were all banking on this. And he said, yes, you can go. So they went. T
hinking to get - thinking on Friday when they get their pay they'd have full pay. But no, nothing doing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I - either five or eight shillings a week for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you feel this was a f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ir wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Well I didn't - I didn't know exactly what should have at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 All.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, put in the - in the - cashiers box, and you know with the family - family expenditure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
The mill? Rather frightened I was, so many girls there. I was frightened stiff of them, yes. I dare not come over and sit down with 'em. 'Cos there was so many of 'em. Oh I was afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What were you afraid of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Frightened of them. Oh they were tough. Yes, I always wait 'til the girls go. And all the sound of their voices disappear and then I'd - I'd let them have a good start yes, and I was such a shy little boy at the time. Oh dear dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well he didn't treat me much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well what is it - I can't remember what I had. What - what wages did he pay to me, five shillings or ten shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did he treat you in work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh - no, he wasn't a bit friendly. I used to call in his house of a Saturday morning and he was all over mother. But - in - in the - in the works he was a very different man. But I've got no complaints about that. I mean - I mean you've got to keep 
your position.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh I think I - well as long as he was giving me - couple of bob a week I didn't trouble
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well it was filthy work. All this wool - went - you know, I told you 
about the wool being ripped up and it's - it's - oiled, for so - put on the floor and for every so many pounds of wool, so much oil's got to be - put into it. You've got a can of oil now and - got a - well you had the wool, put your hand in the can and sp
r
inkle the oil all over it. Then the next bale comes and same again. And you pick it all up, the four or five layers like that, equally. To put in the machines, make sure - make sure now the oil is through everything. Then you carried out, and by carrying 
it out you were - you know, by the end of the week - all oil was through to my body. Through all my clothes. This oil. Quite healthy - oil is - olive oil. But - filthy job. Oh dear it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you like the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh yes. I did like it, I like it because I had a couple of bob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were saying something about when the factory inspector called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Of course everybody that - that goes to work in a factory or works has got to pass the doctor. And his name entered on the factory register. Well I'd 
been there sometime now and - I - hadn't been asked - I hadn't been asked to - be - examined by the doctor at all. So one day inspector of factories called. And that was enough. John Phillips said, he said to me, well, he said to me, hey, you'd better cle
ar out, he said. Don't want the factory inspector to see you because you haven't been certified. That mean I didn't book see. So I had the afternoon off. He let me go home see. Anyway - what was I coming to now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You quite liked the job anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What jobs have you done then after that, you moved after the war to Davids didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Was there many years. I can't remember how many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't have a job between the flannel factory and D.R. David's.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Then you went into the office then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 D.R. David's office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 There was no prospect in the flannel factory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I wouldn't have taken if it was. Filthy place - and the money was small. If that was the rate they'd pay you you'd never get married.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So that's only the one job you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
No, I - I was - and I'll tell you that story now. After this - this oil episode, factory inspector called. And I hadn't been certified. Oh that's all right then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't have another job besides the flannel factory and D.R. David's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No, I stick - I stayed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You had an office job at D.R. David's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What exactly did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - enter - well I don't know, I went on the - shipping and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 And D.R. David's was tinplate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Tinplates, yes. I had to do - do all the office work, you know, office boy's work, enter - enter the letters into envelops and stamp them and keep a record of stamps and all the rest of it. And help with the pay book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Eventually you were in charge of the office when you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you have preferred another type of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 I was quite satisfied there. Although the money wasn't much but - you know - as long you'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 e comfortable you can put up with a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have to have any training for any of your jobs or serve an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. Only I did was - take a course of book keeping that kind of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Or a professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. I mean - you don't mean clubs or that kind of thing? No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Did you feel that there were any divisions of interest among workers, some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and 
other workers, did you feel that, you were in the mill and then D.R. Davids, what was the attitude in the mill between the skilled men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In the old - the free}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 In D.R. David's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh - well in - not too many skilled men in - in the tin wo
rks, you see. Only the fitter - and the smith. That's all. Well all the rest of the men are - in the mill. Which - which - yes, which anybody can do only - you know, be trained to it. There's no special - privilege there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't feel here was any division between workers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, I think so. You always had something to look forward to. You always - there's something to do - with a job. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When you left school you continued to live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were in West End then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 West End, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 When you started full time work did you change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. I - I mean - as is often then the parents were then as were previously.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It didn't make any difference?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You didn't feel any differently now you were bringing a wage home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about with your brothers and sisters, when you first went to work how did you feel with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Oh I - felt - mighty important I tell you. 'Course I had a brother older than me working. Of course I couldn't have all the - say, he was bringing his wages in as well, but the others were
 younger than me. They were - they had nothing to say because they wasn't bringing any cash in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How did you feel now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh important. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about with your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Oh well - it was - usual natural way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you spend Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Best clothes on first thing on Sunday morning. Went to church in the morning. Sunday school in the afternoon. And - time for tea, and then church in the night. And - that'd be after service on Sunday nights we'd have o
ur best clothes and go round about and such as that. That kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 It was the same after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes, we - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. We used to - have a bit of fun of the - on the p
olling days, like the rest of the people. The funny things about it - local elections - Charlie Jenkins used to leave and - a handcart outside his shop in High Street, Taibach, and sure as eggs - the following night - somebody would pinch the handcart and
 run it round the town. What for I don't know. Devilment more than anything else you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you didn't actually take part in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 About how you spent your spare time when you started work, you were telling me about the football you belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes, I was Secretary - Secretary of the - of the football - of the church football club. And we had a - we could spend a lot of time with that. And we had other meetings of temperance society and so on. Attached to the church. A
nd it was most enjoyable between the lot of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You were Secretary of the football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Yes. And - and - what they told me home I was only wasting my time. Better I sat down and - and tried to learn something than run about looking for a ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What was it you were saying about the rough team?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Played - against all the local sides, and our greatest rivals were a church team. St Mary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s. In one match - five players were ordered off. For rough play. And news of this must have travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ed very fast, for the following Saturday - when St Theodore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s team arrived at Porthcawl to play, the Chairman of that team approached the horse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 brake - as soon as we had stopped, telling the captain, if you intend playing the same type of game - as the one you played last Saturday against St Mary}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 
\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
s Aberanon, you had better remain in the brake. We don't want any of that in Porthcawl. Oh wait a minute. After promises of - good conduct we made the game commenced. And it was soon discovered that Porthcawl team was taking 
advantage of this promise, and they come in very rough. The Saints put up with it - under this treatment until half time. After which they retaliated, and the game ended in an uproar. Even the St Theodore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s umpire - having his bowler hat knocked down over 
his eyes in the fray. While trying to restore peace and - order. Bill Owen. Somebody came behind him and hit him on the head, hit his hat down. Yes. Yes. Money was always a problem. Had - and at a meeting where the team's finances were discussed a suggest
ion was made that the vicar should be asked to subscribe to the funds. One of the members volunt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
ered to approach the vicar on this subject, and when asked what he would - say to the vicar he replied, please Mr Vicar Jones, will you put something against our team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What about the big adventure you had with the football team in 1910?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well, a Cardiff football team - often played against St Theodore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s, at Port Talbot, which suited the - the home team as it meant - less expense than trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 ll}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ing to Cardiff. This club had played a few matches in France, and offered to put St Theodore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 s team in touch with some French clubs. St Theodore}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
s team eventually arranged fixtures with Portiere and Viersone on Shrove Tuesday and Ash Wednesday February the 9th and 10th, 1910, winning both matches. This was a wonderful experience for youngsters in those days. The Secretary of St Theodore}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
s team was in the employ of Major David at the time, obtained a loan from him, to cover expenses. And on receipt of this guarantee - g
uaranteed accounts from the French team we - he was repaid. After all the arrangements had been made a rumour was heard in Taibach that Vicar Jones was annoyed because a church team was travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15759364\charrsid14304431 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 ing to France on a Sunday. It was only a - cook and bull story.
 It was quite untrue. The Vicar offered to hold a Holy Communion service and - at six a.m. - and all because a church team was travelling Sunday wasn't it. It was quite untrue. And the Vicar offered to hold the Holy Communion service at 6 a.m. prior to th
e team's departure on the 9 a.m. train. The Chairman and Vice-Chairman of the club, Sergeant Nash and Mr W.R. Owen acted as servers at the service. Well that's the end of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What happened then after the service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 After the service we went home and got ready for the - for the London train then at nine o'clock. What did we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You then went Newhaven-Dieppe, it was a wonderful experience to have wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 How many of you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Sixteen. Only fifteen of us, I was - I was - manager, umpire, first reserve. And last reserve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You weren't playing in the team then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 You used to play a lot of football didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you ever go again or was it just the one trip to France?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
Once, yes. And the - we - we were guaranteed three hundred frances. I think it was three hundred, I don't remember now, it was round about three hundred frances. Lot of money it seemed - it seemed a lot of money paper but it doesn't work out a lot. We had
 to put something towards that to - cover the expenses. We came back in debt. But we worked the debt off. Gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you stay in the homes of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No. No. No, we had a hotel. Oh lived like - lords there. And - I was only a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 So you were spending a lot of your spare time with the football team?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Was there anything else you did in your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well I was in all the societies connected with the church, temperance - temperance - temperance and all the rest of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you go out in the evenings, just to church and football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Who did you go with then, who were your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 John \{BLANK\} was one. He was - I don't know how we were fixed up when he - married my wife's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you make new friends when you left school and started work, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 No, just seemed to be - in a rut, the same - same ones you see all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you take friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes, on occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did you have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well - boys living near me and we used to go to school together and that kind of thing schoolmates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 But you still kept on with them after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
In a way, yes, they - we - only had to satisfy them that - we never kept late hours as youngsters. So there was no need for them to worry as to - they didn't - they had no worries as regards our - after - after meetings or anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Did they expect you to be home by a certain time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 
They didn't look upon coming home late - in a very nice light. But they never said anything, I mean, the manner - the manner was sufficient to guard against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5270513 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10378257 WG  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4263350\charrsid14304431 Well half past nine. Yes. 'Cos very often - when I got in - it was maybe going up twenty to ten, you see, ten minutes late.
